Guludo Beach Lodge, located on a 12km stretch of deserted white beach overlooking the Quirimbas Archipelago in Mozambique, is a small eco lodge which was set up to demonstrate how successful integrating philanthropy into a tourism business could be. The lodge employs the majority of its staff locally and has invested in the professional development of local staff since it started and it uses over 150 local lodge suppliers who sell seafood, fruit, vegetables and more on a daily basis. It partners with Helvetas, which helps small-scale farmers in Mozambique to build storage facilities, train families to cultivate, harvest and store staple crops, while also providing seeds of improved varieties with a shorter vegetative period. Finally, an agricultural technician has established four village farmers’ associations, involving 120 families who have received technical support and equipment, such as irrigation pedal pumps. #init4thelongrun 📷 - Guludo Beach Lodge

B.L.D.E. Association's A.S. Patil College of Commerce (BLDEA-ASPCC), Vijayapura was established in 1961 under the aegis of B.L.D.E Associations. It has been re-accredited by NAAC with 'A' grade. The college is an autonomous institution from the academic year 2008-09, it will be geared to provide an excellent education to all those who enter its precincts. As a center of learning their goal at the college is to train individuals to become men and women of integrity with a strong set of values.

The vision of the college is to emerge as a premier autonomous institution offering commerce, management, entrepreneurship and computer education with service to mankind. Their mission is to provide a strong edifice in nurturing an environment for the holistic growth of learners and contribute to the nation building activities.
